        <div class="column">
          <h3>
            What's New?
          </h3>
          <div class="rounded clearfix" id="whats-new">
            <div class="content">
              <h5>
                SchoolTool 2.8.4 Released, SchoolTool 3.0 Announced
              </h5>
              <p>
              <a href="http://sielibre.com">SIELibre, LLC</a> has released 
              SchoolTool 2.8.4, a bugfix release 
              of our free student information system.  This release addresses 
              two issues: </p>
              <ul class="uses">
                <li>
                  <a href="https://bugs.launchpad.net/schooltool.gradebook/+bug/1432672">
                1432672</a> -- report cards omitting grades under certain 
                circumstances;</li>
                <li>
                  <a href="https://bugs.launchpad.net/schooltool/+bug/1436881">
                  1436881</a> -- comment dialog not working with certain 
                browsers.</li>
                </ul>

              <p>SIELibre is planning to release a major update, SchoolTool 3.0,
                in the third quarter of 2015, including a completely redesigned
                "School" page, which streamlines common administrative tasks,
                and a student fee tracking system.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/u/1/d/1bTpy5elxDty6LgbHu04Zxk0liVetJ7Xu1qQ6WsXCsBA/pub"
               class="learn right">
              read more...
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <h3>
            How to get started.
          </h3>
          <div class="rounded clearfix" id="how-to-get-started">
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Simple, automated
                installation and updates are provided for SchoolTool on
                <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/">Ubuntu Linux</a>.
              </p>
 
              <p>
                If you are not already running Ubuntu, you can
                <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/download/ubuntu/download">download</a>
                and install it on a hard drive, or just test it
                running on a CD or USB stick.
              </p>
              <p>
                SchoolTool can be hosted on a PC or server at the
                school site, or a remote server in "the cloud."
              </p>
              <p>SchoolTool and Ubuntu Linux are free software, so you 
                 can run it with no licensing fees to serve as many schools
                 as you like.  SchoolTool is distributed under the terms of 
                 the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html">GNU 
                 General Public License v2.0</a>.</p>
                 <hr />
                               <p>
                Commercial support, hosting and custom development for 
                SchoolTool  are
                available from <a href="http://sielibre.com">SIELibre,
                LLC</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a href="http://book.schooltool.org/system-requirements.html"
               class="learn right">
              learn more...
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <h3>
            Who uses SchoolTool?
          </h3>
          <div class="rounded clearfix" id="who-uses-schooltool">
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                SchoolTool is part of ambitious technology deployments
                on six continents, including:
              </p>
              <ul class="uses">
                <li>
                  <a href="http://sielibre.com">SIELibre</a> has worked with 
                  UK-based
                  charity <a href="http://www.arkonline.org/">Absolute
                  Return for Kids (ARK)</a> to create a customized version of
                  SchoolTool for <a href= "http://www.peas.org.uk/">PEAS
                  schools</a> in Uganda and a network of schools in India.
                  Read more about this work on the blog of <a href="http://www.bringmoredata.blogspot.co.uk/2014/07/you-want-free-school-information-system.html">Joshua Perry, Director of Programme Support for 
              ARK Schools</a>.
                </li>

                <li>
                  <a href="http://www.cteresource.org/">The Virginia
                  CTE Resource Center</a> supports over 30 sites using
                  CanDo to manage competency tracking.
                </li>
                <li>
                The <a href="http://www.baiacademy.org/">Burundi American 
                International Academy</a> in Kinindo,
                Burundi uses SchoolTool as their primary student information
                system and contracts with 
                <a href="http://sielibre.com">SIELibre</a> for hosting and
                support services. 
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
